 * ================================================================================================
 * this program reads list of number ordered in rows from a file input and stores it in a struct. 
 * then the program calculates the biggest row value which is the row that contain the biggest 
 * value in its colomns compared to all other rows colomns and prints it to the output file. if no
 * such row -1 is printed.
 * ================================================================================================
 * Compile: gcc -Wall ex0.c -o ex0
 * Run: ./ex0 input-file
 * Run time: o(n^2)
 ==================================================================================================
